=== Approach ===
[[File:Ninomiya-Shrine.JPG|thumb|200px|right|Sando]]
When you approach the shrine from the torii gate in front of the shrine, the approach becomes lower and then crosses the valley. Furthermore, a stream flows at the bottom of the valley, and the water vein is said to lead to a pond within the grounds of {{ill|lt=Kikuta Shrine|Q11619900|WD=Q11619900|1=Kikuta Shrine}}, which is enshrined in {{ill|lt=Tsudanuma|Q7849928|WD=Q7849928|1=Tsudanuma}} in {{ill|lt=Narashino City|Q318047|WD=Q318047|1=Narashino}}. If you walk along the valley floor in a straight line, by the time you reach the top of the stone steps, you will be able to see the Karahafu facing the worship hall, and the master carpenter's {{ill|lt=Design|Q82604|WD=Q82604|1=Design}} has been ingenious so that you can take your time to admire the large, majestic {{ill|lt=Karagohafu|Q977293|WD=Q977293|1=Karahafu}} curves and the majestic carvings.

=== Festival ===
* {{ill|lt=Saidan Festival|Q11546824|WD=Q11546824|1=Saitan-sai}} (January 1st)
* Oshahatsu Festival (January 7th)
* Otsutsu porridge cooking ritual (January 14th)
* {{ill|lt=Setsubun|Q746798|WD=Q746798|lt=Setsubun Festival|1=Setsubun}} (February 3rd)
* '''Regular Festival''' (October 16th)
* '''Daikaage'' (Obiyo, {{ill|lt=lunar calendar|Q11511066|WD=Q11511066|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar}}night of November 13th)
:A festival named after the bonfires lit by villagers to welcome Fujiwara no Moritsune and others who were said to have been exiled to this area.
* '''{{ill|lt=Seven Year Festival of Shimousa Sanzan|Q11361280|WD=Q11361280|1=Shimōsa Miyama Seven-Year Festival}}''' (Year of the Ox/Year of the Wild)
:A festival held once every seven years, centered around our company, with nine shrines in Funabashi City, {{ill|lt=Chiba City|Q170616|WD=Q170616|1=Chiba (city)}}, {{ill|lt=Yachiyo City|Q328651|WD=Q328651|1=Yachiyo, Chiba}}, and Narashino City participating. Our company plays the role of "father."

=== Surroundings ===
* '''{{ill|lt=Jinguji Temple (Funabashi City)|Q11589481|WD=Q11589481|lt=Douzan Jinguji Temple|1=Jingū-ji}}'''
: Adjacent. Our company {{ill|lt=Bettoji Temple|Q11396755|WD=Q11396755|1=Bettō-ji}} before {{ill|lt=Haibutsu Kishaku|Q702298|WD=Q702298|1=Haibutsu kishaku}}.

