* Ginkgo at Ninomiya Shrine (natural monument) - Designated on March 30, 2012.

=== Transportation access ===
* {{ill|lt=Tsudanuma Station|Q801534|WD=Q801534|1=Tsudanuma Station}} ({{ill|lt=East Japan Railway Company|Q499071|WD=Q499071|lt=JR East|1=East Japan Railway Company}}{{ill|lt=Sobu Main Line|Q1191364|WD=Q1191364|1=Sōbu Main Line}}) From the north exit
** Take the {{ill|lt=Keisei Bus|Q11374367|WD=Q11374367|1=Keisei Bus}} (Tsu 02 bound for Ninomiya Shrine) and get off at the final stop, "Ninomiya Shrine" (ride time: 20 minutes)
** Take the {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Funabashi Shinkeisei Bus|1=UNKNOWN}} (Tsu 08 bound for Ninomiya Jinja-mae) and get off at the final stop, "Ninomiya-jinja-mae" (20 minute ride)
* From {{ill|lt=Yakuendai Station|Q8047226|WD=Q8047226|1=Yakuendai Station}} ({{ill|lt=Keisei Matsudo Line|Q3553734|WD=Q3553734|1=Keisei Matsudo Line}})
** Walk (3 minutes) from the Yakuendai Station Iriguchi bus stop on National Route 296, take the {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Funabashi Shinkeisei Bus|1=UNKNOWN}} (Tsu 08 bound for Ninomiya Jinja-mae) and get off at the final stop, Ninomiya-jinja-mae (10 minute ride)
* From {{ill|lt=Keisei Okubo Station|Q6383851|WD=Q6383851|1=Keisei Ōkubo Station}} ({{ill|lt=Keisei Main Line|Q1063675|WD=Q1063675|1=Keisei Main Line}})
** Walk (7 minutes) from the Toho Daigaku-mae bus stop, take {{ill|lt=Keisei Bus|Q11374367|WD=Q11374367|1=Keisei Bus}} (Tsu 02 bound for Ninomiya Shrine) and get off at the final stop, Ninomiya Shrine (ride time: 6 minutes)
*: Keisei buses near Keisei Okubo Station have different routes for going down and going up. The nearest bus stop for going down is "Toho Daigaku-mae" and the nearest bus stop for going up is "Okubo Jujiro".

